1
00:00:01,134 --> 00:00:02,435
Krone: Hmm?

2
00:00:02,503 --> 00:00:05,306
Gilda: Join forces?

3
00:00:06,406 --> 00:00:07,607
Norman: It’s fine, you guys.

4
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:09,543
- No need to worry.
- ( All gasp )

5
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:11,345
Norman: We’ll hear you out.

6
00:00:11,411 --> 00:00:14,714
( Krone chuckles )

7
00:00:14,781 --> 00:00:17,517
excellent.
It’s best if we cooperate

8
00:00:17,584 --> 00:00:19,753
so we can each
achieve our goals.

9
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:22,356
you all want
to break out of here,

10
00:00:22,422 --> 00:00:25,659
and I want to eventually
become mom of this house.

11
00:00:27,227 --> 00:00:30,363
The plan is to drag Isabella
from her position

12
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:32,365
and then seize it for myself.

13
00:00:32,432 --> 00:00:33,800
Don: You wanna be a mom?

14
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,635
Krone: To prove that I mean it,

15
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:39,139
you kids aren’t the only ones
who wanna break free from this.

16
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:41,641
( All gasp )

17
00:00:45,145 --> 00:00:46,279
♪

18
00:00:46,346 --> 00:00:48,448
( Singing in Japanese )

19
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:04,431
♪ Fire

20
00:01:04,498 --> 00:01:06,633
( singing in Japanese )

21
00:01:30,657 --> 00:01:33,226
krone: Are you aware
of the management system here?

22
00:01:33,293 --> 00:01:35,195
( All gasp )

23
00:01:35,262 --> 00:01:36,697
Krone: Girls who meet
certain conditions

24
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:39,466
and live until the age of 12
are usually presented

25
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:42,436
with two different paths when
they’re about to be shipped out,

26
00:01:42,503 --> 00:01:46,440
continue and die
or aim to become a mom.

27
00:01:46,507 --> 00:01:48,142
Don: What conditions?

28
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:50,744
Krone: High test scores
and the mom’s recommendation.

29
00:01:50,811 --> 00:01:52,613
Meet those two requirements,

30
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:56,249
and it’s possible to survive
without escaping,

31
00:01:56,316 --> 00:01:57,317
if you’re a girl.

32
00:01:57,384 --> 00:01:58,552
Gilda: Only girls?

33
00:01:58,619 --> 00:02:02,089
Krone: Although,
I don’t recommend it.

34
00:02:02,155 --> 00:02:05,492
They make it so you’re never
allowed to leave the premises.

35
00:02:07,528 --> 00:02:08,596
( All gasp )

36
00:02:08,662 --> 00:02:09,763
Emma: What is that?

37
00:02:09,830 --> 00:02:12,099
Krone: There’s a chip inside,

38
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:15,603
and, with it, if you step
one foot outside the farm,

39
00:02:15,669 --> 00:02:20,240
an electric current triggers
and causes your heart to stop.

40
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,241
( All gasp )

41
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:22,810
Krone: But, at the same time,

42
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:25,178
if your heart stops
for some other reason,

43
00:02:25,245 --> 00:02:28,582
it acts as a transmitter
that notifies the higher-ups.

44
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:31,185
Norman: We were right about
not being able to kill them.

45
00:02:31,251 --> 00:02:32,686
( Krone chuckles )

46
00:02:32,753 --> 00:02:36,223
because of this chip,
I can only live on the farms.

47
00:02:36,290 --> 00:02:37,424
That’s why I wanna live

48
00:02:37,491 --> 00:02:39,393
in the best way
this place has to offer.

49
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:41,795
- ( Emma sighs )
- Krone: Even if it’s fake,

50
00:02:41,862 --> 00:02:44,565
being a mom means
you get to feel human,

51
00:02:44,631 --> 00:02:48,368
but, to achieve that,
I have to remove Isabella.

52
00:02:48,435 --> 00:02:52,673
If all of you escape, she’ll be
the one who’s blamed for it.

53
00:02:52,739 --> 00:02:54,608
( Giggles ) Trust me,

54
00:02:54,675 --> 00:02:57,244
i won’t stop you
if you make a run for it.

55
00:02:57,311 --> 00:02:59,446
It actually benefits me.

56
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:00,781
Gilda: You won’t ship us out?

57
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:02,483
- Krone: Of course not.
- ( Gilda and Don gasp )

58
00:03:02,549 --> 00:03:05,152
Krone: So let’s cooperate!

59
00:03:05,219 --> 00:03:06,253
( Don groans )

60
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,555
( Emma grunts )

61
00:03:07,621 --> 00:03:09,323
( Norman sighs )

62
00:03:11,124 --> 00:03:12,125
( Krone chuckles )

63
00:03:15,229 --> 00:03:16,330
How about it?

64
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,734
Emma: Norman.

65
00:03:21,835 --> 00:03:23,070
Wait a sec.

66
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:24,638
I wanna make sure of something.

67
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:25,773
Krone: What is it?

68
00:03:25,839 --> 00:03:27,307
Krone: How can we be sure

69
00:03:27,374 --> 00:03:29,176
you’re not gonna
betray us in the end?

70
00:03:29,243 --> 00:03:31,378
Krone: Are you saying
you don’t trust me?

71
00:03:31,445 --> 00:03:32,780
Emma: Answer!

72
00:03:32,846 --> 00:03:34,181
( Krone scoffs )

73
00:03:34,248 --> 00:03:35,483
All right.

74
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:38,118
if ray goes
and tattles on me to mom,

75
00:03:38,185 --> 00:03:39,753
you can destroy me.

76
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:43,590
Meanwhile, if I tell mom that
ray’s acting as a double agent,

77
00:03:43,657 --> 00:03:46,160
then all of you
will go down with him.

78
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:48,729
so, you see,
neither of us will snitch,

79
00:03:48,795 --> 00:03:50,797
because we can’t.

80
00:03:50,864 --> 00:03:52,566
Do you trust me now?

81
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:53,567
( Emma sighs )

82
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:58,505
Yeah, sure.

83
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:01,008
Krone: I guess
we have a deal, then.

84
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:04,411
♪

85
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:14,454
( Chuckles )

86
00:04:14,521 --> 00:04:16,523
I know a lot of info
about this place

87
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,358
that may be helpful
for you to know,

88
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:20,527
and i’m willing
to share it with you all.

89
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:23,163
It’s proof of my goodwill.
If you’re interested,

90
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:25,632
why don’t you
drop by my room tonight?

91
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:28,769
( Children chattering,
laughing )

92
00:04:34,474 --> 00:04:35,775
Emma: She was one of us,

93
00:04:35,843 --> 00:04:39,180
and yet this is just
so she can have a better life.

94
00:04:39,246 --> 00:04:41,248
What a monster.
She doesn’t care

95
00:04:41,315 --> 00:04:43,517
if any of the kids here
live or die at all.

96
00:04:43,584 --> 00:04:45,419
gilda: She said
she won’t ship us, though.

97
00:04:45,485 --> 00:04:48,655
Norman: What she meant
was she can’t.

98
00:04:48,722 --> 00:04:51,124
If she really
wanted us to escape,

99
00:04:51,191 --> 00:04:53,326
then she would have
quietly helped us.

100
00:04:53,393 --> 00:04:55,629
the only reason
she’s showing us her cards

101
00:04:55,696 --> 00:04:58,065
is to try to gain our trust.

102
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:00,233
Don: What’s the point
in doing that?

103
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:04,037
Norman: It’s all so she can get
solid evidence of our rebellion.

104
00:05:04,104 --> 00:05:06,039
In other words,
she’s in a position

105
00:05:06,106 --> 00:05:07,608
where the higher-ups
won’t trust her

106
00:05:07,674 --> 00:05:09,676
unless she has proof.

107
00:05:09,743 --> 00:05:13,146
She doesn’t have the power
to ship us out like mom does.

108
00:05:13,213 --> 00:05:15,549
- Gilda: Evidence?
- ( Don gasps ) Wait.

109
00:05:15,616 --> 00:05:18,519
What happens if she finds
the rope we hid in the tree?!

110
00:05:18,585 --> 00:05:21,221
norman: It’s fine.
Explaining the rope is easy.

111
00:05:21,288 --> 00:05:24,057
We can say we were gonna use it
for a game, but if we--

112
00:05:24,124 --> 00:05:26,627
ray: If she finds the tools
to break the trackers,

113
00:05:26,693 --> 00:05:28,295
then we’re done for.

114
00:05:28,362 --> 00:05:31,065
Norman: That kind of evidence
would be hard to explain.

115
00:05:31,131 --> 00:05:32,466
( Don and gilda gasp )

116
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:34,135
Ray: No need to worry.

117
00:05:34,201 --> 00:05:35,803
I’m not gonna let that happen.

118
00:05:35,869 --> 00:05:38,338
I’m not finished
making it yet, anyway.

119
00:05:38,405 --> 00:05:40,674
Norman: That won’t be an issue
if we can convince her

120
00:05:40,741 --> 00:05:43,477
that we don’t know where
they are or how to break them.

121
00:05:43,544 --> 00:05:46,080
I’m sure sister krone
would believe us

122
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:48,081
if we play our cards right.

123
00:05:48,148 --> 00:05:50,283
Gilda: You’re going to her room?

124
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,119
you’re dealing
with sister krone here.

125
00:05:53,187 --> 00:05:56,057
it’s nice she offered
to give us information, but--

126
00:05:56,123 --> 00:05:58,592
don: Hang on.
Why are we cooperating with her?

127
00:05:58,659 --> 00:06:00,427
Does it give us an advantage?

128
00:06:00,494 --> 00:06:02,663
Norman: If we
use her effectively,

129
00:06:02,729 --> 00:06:04,598
we might learn something useful.

130
00:06:04,665 --> 00:06:07,001
additionally,
it’ll keep her out of the way

131
00:06:07,067 --> 00:06:09,236
so we can focus
on the inspection.

132
00:06:09,303 --> 00:06:11,172
( Don sighs )

133
00:06:11,238 --> 00:06:12,239
( Grunts )

134
00:06:12,306 --> 00:06:13,774
( Gilda sighs )

135
00:06:13,841 --> 00:06:15,643
Emma: We’ll be fine.

136
00:06:15,709 --> 00:06:19,379
we have to use
every opportunity that we can!

137
00:06:19,446 --> 00:06:21,415
( Laughs )

138
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:22,415
( Gilda sighs )

139
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:24,651
( Norman chuckles )

140
00:06:28,789 --> 00:06:30,591
- ( Don sighs )
- ( Norman grunts )

141
00:06:30,657 --> 00:06:31,591
Don: Hmm.

142
00:06:33,861 --> 00:06:35,763
Norman: Ray, can I talk to you?

143
00:06:35,829 --> 00:06:38,298
I want to discuss
the investigation.

144
00:06:38,365 --> 00:06:39,399
Ray: Okay.

145
00:06:41,602 --> 00:06:42,803
( Door opens )

146
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:44,305
( Door closes )

147
00:06:44,371 --> 00:06:47,207
Emma: I have a favor
I want to ask of you guys.

148
00:06:57,551 --> 00:06:59,453
( Clock ticking )

149
00:07:00,654 --> 00:07:03,991
( Tape rips )

150
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:17,605
( Both grunt )

151
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:22,042
( Footsteps approaching )

152
00:07:27,514 --> 00:07:29,416
( Both sigh )

153
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,488
( Door creaks )

154
00:07:34,555 --> 00:07:36,490
♪

155
00:07:42,329 --> 00:07:46,166
Krone: We’re allies now,
so ask me anything.

156
00:07:47,234 --> 00:07:49,570
( Both gasp )

157
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,171
Krone: Hmm?

158
00:07:51,238 --> 00:07:52,306
( Emma grunts )

159
00:07:52,372 --> 00:07:54,074
Norman: We can ask
whatever we want?

160
00:07:54,141 --> 00:07:58,479
Krone: Yes. It can be about
the farm or even headquarters.

161
00:07:58,545 --> 00:08:00,213
( Clock ticking )

162
00:08:01,515 --> 00:08:03,317
- Norman: Then...
- Emma: Show it to us,

163
00:08:03,383 --> 00:08:06,019
the thing that receives signal
from our trackers.

164
00:08:06,086 --> 00:08:07,387
Krone: Ohh.

165
00:08:09,089 --> 00:08:10,190
( Chuckles )

166
00:08:11,692 --> 00:08:14,728
Oh. Of course.

167
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:33,647
There’s not a lot to it,
is there?

168
00:08:33,714 --> 00:08:37,651
It shows the current location,
but doesn’t say who it is.

169
00:08:37,718 --> 00:08:40,254
( Both sigh )

170
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:43,023
Krone: So you knew that there
were tracking devices?

171
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:45,759
norman: Yeah.
We found out from mom,

172
00:08:45,826 --> 00:08:49,163
but we don’t know where they are
or how to destroy them.

173
00:08:49,229 --> 00:08:50,597
Emma: Do you know, sister?

174
00:08:50,664 --> 00:08:52,599
krone: Yes.
They’re found in your ear.

175
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:53,600
( Both gasp )

176
00:08:53,667 --> 00:08:55,569
Krone: Around here, on the left.

177
00:08:55,636 --> 00:08:57,338
( Both sigh )

178
00:08:58,805 --> 00:08:59,739
Krone: Hmm.

179
00:09:01,175 --> 00:09:03,244
I don’t really know
how to break them,

180
00:09:03,310 --> 00:09:05,179
but I do know that,
if they’re broken,

181
00:09:05,245 --> 00:09:08,081
it notifies
the tracking tool and hq,

182
00:09:10,217 --> 00:09:12,119
♪

183
00:09:12,186 --> 00:09:15,690
You’d either have to take it out
or just cut that part off.

184
00:09:15,756 --> 00:09:18,525
norman: How?
There are no sharp blades here.

185
00:09:18,592 --> 00:09:20,327
Krone: There is one, a scalpel.

186
00:09:20,394 --> 00:09:22,563
norman:
There’s no medicine outside,

187
00:09:22,629 --> 00:09:24,431
and I don’t
wanna start our escape

188
00:09:24,498 --> 00:09:26,433
with blood loss or infections.

189
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,735
Krone: The infirmary
has medicine

190
00:09:27,801 --> 00:09:30,170
and anesthesia you could use,

191
00:09:30,237 --> 00:09:31,538
tools as well.

192
00:09:31,605 --> 00:09:35,542
Now, the supplies should last
at least five kids.

193
00:09:35,609 --> 00:09:37,711
I can teach you how to use them.

194
00:09:37,778 --> 00:09:39,747
I’ll even lend you the key.

195
00:09:39,813 --> 00:09:42,549
Since that’s settled,
anything else?

196
00:09:42,616 --> 00:09:45,052
( Both sigh )

197
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:46,453
Emma: How old are you, exactly,

198
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:49,156
and have you
always been a product?

199
00:09:49,223 --> 00:09:50,658
Krone: Mm-mm-mm.

200
00:09:50,724 --> 00:09:54,194
It’s pretty rude of you
to ask a lady her age,

201
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:57,030
but i’m gonna
let it slide this time.

202
00:09:57,097 --> 00:10:00,767
I’m 26. I was born and raised
at this house,

203
00:10:00,834 --> 00:10:03,136
though not here
at plant three, mind you.

204
00:10:03,203 --> 00:10:04,538
Norman: There’s more than one?

205
00:10:04,605 --> 00:10:06,574
Krone: And from what
I saw in the records,

206
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:09,243
it seems isabella’s 31.

207
00:10:09,309 --> 00:10:11,344
norman: Tell me,
have you seen the outside?

208
00:10:11,411 --> 00:10:12,779
- Krone: Not once.
- ( Both gasp )

209
00:10:12,846 --> 00:10:16,650
Krone: Oh? Did you think
that i’d lie and say yes?

210
00:10:16,717 --> 00:10:19,119
- I haven’t.
- ( Norman sighs )

211
00:10:19,186 --> 00:10:21,188
Krone: But there are
humans out there.

212
00:10:21,255 --> 00:10:23,190
The higher-ups and us adults

213
00:10:23,257 --> 00:10:25,726
make all the food
that you kids eat.

214
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:27,294
However, there are humans

215
00:10:27,361 --> 00:10:30,231
who bring your clothes
and supplies from outside.

216
00:10:30,297 --> 00:10:32,599
I’ve seen them
at headquarters once,

217
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:34,501
and it seemed like they were

218
00:10:34,568 --> 00:10:36,703
all in equal standing
with each other.

219
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:39,306
What you all need to do
is get mixed in

220
00:10:39,373 --> 00:10:41,108
with the humans
who won’t get eaten.

221
00:10:41,175 --> 00:10:42,109
( Both sigh )

222
00:10:42,176 --> 00:10:45,446
Emma: So just how long...

223
00:10:45,512 --> 00:10:47,514
Have the demons been around?

224
00:10:47,581 --> 00:10:48,515
Krone: "Demons"?

225
00:10:48,582 --> 00:10:50,484
Oh, you must mean them.

226
00:10:50,551 --> 00:10:53,254
Emma: And how did
the world get like this?

227
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,321
If you know.

228
00:10:54,388 --> 00:10:55,322
Krone: I don’t.

229
00:10:55,389 --> 00:10:56,557
( Emma gasps )

230
00:10:56,623 --> 00:10:58,091
( Norman sighs )

231
00:11:02,729 --> 00:11:04,264
Emma: Where is
this house located?

232
00:11:04,331 --> 00:11:05,365
Krone: No idea.

233
00:11:05,432 --> 00:11:06,767
Norman: What about the security?

234
00:11:06,834 --> 00:11:09,070
Krone: Now, that, I know.

235
00:11:09,136 --> 00:11:10,471
There isn’t too much.

236
00:11:10,537 --> 00:11:12,272
they rely
on the tracking devices,

237
00:11:12,339 --> 00:11:14,241
so there aren’t
many guards posted.

238
00:11:14,308 --> 00:11:16,644
I doubt they even patrol.

239
00:11:18,312 --> 00:11:19,246
( Emma grunts )

240
00:11:23,817 --> 00:11:25,585
Norman: Thank you
for all your help.

241
00:11:25,652 --> 00:11:27,254
Krone: Is that it?

242
00:11:27,321 --> 00:11:29,590
Norman: Yeah. Have a good night.

243
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,095
( Krone chuckling )

244
00:11:35,162 --> 00:11:37,097
( Both gasp )

245
00:11:37,164 --> 00:11:39,099
( Krone laughing )

246
00:11:48,475 --> 00:11:51,478
So you already knew
where the trackers were

247
00:11:51,545 --> 00:11:52,813
and how to break them!

248
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,849
I’m actually impressed.

249
00:11:54,915 --> 00:11:57,117
i’ve learned
a lot of interesting things

250
00:11:57,184 --> 00:11:59,620
- during our talk tonight.
- ( Both gasp )

251
00:11:59,686 --> 00:12:03,156
Krone: Info can be provided
without words.

252
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:06,293
Humans tend to give away
a lot of information,

253
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,761
even if they’re
just standing there.

254
00:12:07,828 --> 00:12:11,765
Blinking, gaze,
sweating, attitude,

255
00:12:11,832 --> 00:12:15,235
gestures, pupils, and pulse,

256
